how long after sexual intercourse protected or not can a pregnancy test be taken it depends on when your next period is due if you are regular you can take it up to days before your period is supposed to start using an early pg test such as first response please note only of women test positive days before their period if you're extremely irregular it could take as long as weeks to test but i would safely say that if you're pregnant the test should be accurate approx weeks after sex as this is usually when your hormones would be high enough for the test to work good luck in getting the answer you're looking for Pregnancy Menstrual cycle Oral contraceptive Fertility awareness Sexual intercourse Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Human sexual behavior Birth control Marriage Abortion debate Abortion Emergency contraception Gonorrhoea Pelvic inflammatory disease Pregnancy test Turner syndrome Oral sex Prostate cancer Condom Androgen insensitivity syndrome Obstetrics Breastfeeding Hyperprolactinaemia Child sexuality Orgasm Anal sex Endometriosis Twin Safe sex Teenage pregnancy Sex education Acne Prolactinoma HIV test Miscarriage Ovarian cyst Prenatal diagnosis Rape Polycystic ovary syndrome Human sexuality Extreme Programming Sexual abstinence Sexual dysfunction AIDS Big Brother UK series 6 Intrauterine device Common misconceptions about HIV and AIDS Pornographic movie Sexually-transmitted infection Human height Sex assignment Age of consent Puberty Drug test Fasting Transsexuality Strap-on dildo Haloperidol Password Coeliac disease Infertility Inhibited sexual desire Chemical abortion Cephalic disorder Tocopherol Biology and sexual orientation Variable star Hebrew calendar History of sex Pedophilia Estrus cycle Sexual revolution Growth hormone treatment Breast cancer Social rule Gender role Abduction Phenomenon Bayesian inference Dragons (Pern) Gynecologic hemorrhage Chernobyl accident Masturbation Niddah Omega-3 fatty acid In vitro fertilisation Sexual addiction Relig